=== 专业评价与收视率 ===
节目获得媒体褒贬不一的评价。评论家认为典礼和坎摩尔的主持中规中矩。《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》的{{le|汉克·斯图艾佛|Hank Stuever}}写道：“坎摩尔连续第二年亮相，转播除了要尖刻可靠，什么都不需要，幽默的主持人的表现掌控大局、能言善道，最出色的是——我忘记了。我们不是在缔造娱乐圈的历史，只不过是试着读过又一个奥斯卡之夜罢了。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/tv/a-boring-oscars-show-might-have-helped-soothe-hollywoods-year-of-being-fed-up/2018/03/05/898d2786-1fff-11e8-94da-ebf9d112159c_story.html|title=Review {{!}} That boring Oscars show might have helped soothe Hollywood’s year of being fed up|last=Stuever|first=Hank|date=2018-03-05|work=Washington Post|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305084805/https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/tv/a-boring-oscars-show-might-have-helped-soothe-hollywoods-year-of-being-fed-up/2018/03/05/898d2786-1fff-11e8-94da-ebf9d112159c_story.html|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>《[[纽约_(杂志)|Vulture]]》的{{le|大卫·埃德尔斯坦|David Edelstein}}写道：“这是我所看过的最出色、最鼓舞人心、最纯粹受欢迎的奥斯卡奖转播，它在实际奖项方面也是最令人失望的。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vulture.com/2018/03/oscars-review-an-inspiring-broadcast-disappointing-awards.html|title=Oscars Review: The Most Inspiring Broadcast, the Most Disappointing Awards|last=Edelstein|first=David|work=Vulture|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305122502/http://www.vulture.com/2018/03/oscars-review-an-inspiring-broadcast-disappointing-awards.html|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>《[[名利场_(杂志)|名利场]]》的理查德·劳森（{{lang|en|Richard Lawson}}）写道：“贵为主持，坎摩尔处理得小心谨慎且恰当......总而言之，星期天典礼的表现令人敬佩，承认了围绕在旁的所有动荡，同时保留了愚蠢廉价的包袱，我们许多人都是冲着这些转台看奥斯卡的。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/03/academy-awards-2018-jimmy-kimmel-review|title=The Academy Reckons With the #MeToo Moment in a Long, Charged Oscars Ceremony|last=Lawson|first=Richard|work=HWD|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180308095921/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/03/academy-awards-2018-jimmy-kimmel-review|archivedate=2018-03-08}}</ref>[[美国有线电视新闻网|美国有线电视新闻网]]的布里安·劳利（{{lang|en|Brian Lowry}}）打趣道：“奥斯卡是一头身强体壮的猛兽，总之试着讨好许许多多的大人物。尽管目的是在今年的整个典礼期间，始终保持庆祝基调，既不忽视外部世界，也不冷落房间中的大佬们，主持吉米·坎摩尔和典礼本身非常成功。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/04/entertainment/oscars-review/index.html|title='The Shape of Water' wins, as Oscars tackle the serious without losing the fun|last=CNN|first=Brian Lowry,|work=CNN|access-date=2018-03-05|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305082243/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/04/entertainment/oscars-review/index.html|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>

不过其他人的评论更尖刻。《[[综艺_(杂志)|综艺]]》的{{le|莫琳·瑞恩|Maureen Ryan}}表示：“所有事情都考虑到了，节目气氛还是或多或少地低调。一般来说，节目要花上两个小时才能起到麻木的效果，不过，尽管吉米·坎摩尔表现出色，星期天转播的开场还是让人觉得有点迟钝和疲乏。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://variety.com/2018/tv/columns/oscars-2018-review-academy-awards-jimmy-kimmel-abc-1202717830/|title=TV Review: The 90th Academy Awards Ceremony on ABC|last=Ryan|first=Maureen|date=2018-03-05|work=Variety|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305083342/http://variety.com/2018/tv/columns/oscars-2018-review-academy-awards-jimmy-kimmel-abc-1202717830/|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》电视评论{{le|詹姆斯·波尼沃兹|James Poniewozik}}表示：“尽管目前好莱坞动荡不安，典礼还是主要集中在表面的庆祝和闪光上。处在耀眼的舞台中，典礼似乎被封印在巨大的空间中。臃肿是老大难问题，问题当然是表演的每一个部分都有受众。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/04/movies/some-self-examination-among-the-oscars-self-celebration.html|title=At the Oscars, Some Self-Examination Among the Self-Celebration|date=2018-03-04|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305050547/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/04/movies/some-self-examination-among-the-oscars-self-celebration.html|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的达伦·芬奇（{{lang|en|Darren Franich}}）写道：“我们从今年的奥斯卡中得到了什么乐趣？！确实是又长又臭的表演，但从哪剪呢？<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ew.com/awards/2018/03/05/oscars-2018-review/|title=The 2018 Oscars was a long, political yet cheerful show: EW review|work=EW.com|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305132620/http://ew.com/awards/2018/03/05/oscars-2018-review/|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>”[[Deadline.com|Deadline.com]]格雷格·伊万斯（{{lang|en|Greg Evans}}）：“长达四个小时的节目有没有容纳奥斯卡史上的所有时刻？恐怕没有。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2018/03/oscars-tv-review-jimmy-kimmel-academy-awards-ceremony-donald-trump-1202310869/|title=Oscars TV Review: Jimmy Kimmel Ignores Trump, Hollywood Survives Just Fine|last=Evans|first=Greg|date=2018-03-05|work=Deadline|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305084040/http://deadline.com/2018/03/oscars-tv-review-jimmy-kimmel-academy-awards-ceremony-donald-trump-1202310869/|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>”《[[旧金山纪事报|旧金山纪事报]]》大卫·魏格丹（{{lang|en|David Wiegand}}）：“即便希望拍掌的噪音把观众留在家中，吵醒剧场中的人，除了老戏骨们的入场，其他的毫无亮点<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/tv/article/A-lot-of-political-punches-pulled-in-wearying-12727613.php|title=A lot of political punches thrown in wearying Oscars|work=San Francisco Chronicle|access-date=2018-03-05|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305092521/https://www.sfchronicle.com/tv/article/A-lot-of-political-punches-pulled-in-wearying-12727613.php|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>。”《{{le|俄勒冈人报|The Oregonian}}》专栏作家克里斯蒂·腾奎斯特（{{lang|en|Kristi Turnquist}}）写道：“值得尊敬吗？当然了。这是不是一届沉闷、严肃的奥斯卡颁奖典礼？没错，有点<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/tv/2018/03/2018_oscars_ceremony_diversity.html|title=2018 Oscars: Diversity rules in a show that's respectful, and a bit dull (review)|work=OregonLive.com|access-date=2018-03-05|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305101934/http://www.oregonlive.com/tv/2018/03/2018_oscars_ceremony_diversity.html|archivedate=2018-03-05}}</ref>。”

今年奧斯卡平均收視人口僅2650萬人，與去年相比下降了16%，這是自1974年首次由尼爾森收視調查進行統計以來，奧斯卡頒獎典禮平均收視人口首度跌破3000萬，創下歷史新低，去年雖然也曾創下歷史新低，但仍有3300萬人收看。<ref>{{cite web|title=Oscars 2018 ratings point to a record low|url=http://ew.com/awards/2018/03/05/oscars-2018-ratings/|publisher=EW.com. Retrieved 2018-03-05.|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180306023353/http://ew.com/awards/2018/03/05/oscars-2018-ratings/|archivedate=2018-03-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Oscar Ratings Down Double Digits, Eye All-Time Low In Early Estimates|url=http://deadline.com/2018/03/oscar-ratings-down-all-time-low-viewership-1202310775/|publisher=''Deadline''. Retrieved 2018-03-05.|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180307132956/http://deadline.com/2018/03/oscar-ratings-down-all-time-low-viewership-1202310775/|archivedate=2018-03-07}}</ref>最终收视率公布后，[[美国总统|美国总统]][[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]发布推文：“奥斯卡‘史上’最低收视率！问题是，我们再也没有明星了——除了你们的总统（开玩笑而已，别当真）！<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/971013841395027968|title=President Tweeted regarding Oscars lowest ratings|last=Trump|first=Donald J.|date=2018-03-06|website=@realDonaldTrump|language=en|access-date=2018-03-07|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180306235321/https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/971013841395027968|archivedate=2018-03-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/mar/06/oscars-2018-viewing-figures-for-ceremony-lowest-ever-recorded|title='We don't have stars anymore'; Trump mocks Oscars as ratings fall to record low|last=Mumford|first=Gwilym|date=2018-03-06|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-03-07|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180307053652/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/mar/06/oscars-2018-viewing-figures-for-ceremony-lowest-ever-recorded|archivedate=2018-03-07}}</ref>”坎摩尔则反击：“谢谢你！‘史上’民望最低的总统<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/jimmykimmel/status/971073765567156224?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&ref_url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-et-